snippet.textDisplay: This movie was one big pandering exercise and it frankly makes me sick to see Star Wars in this state. For all the issues people had with TLF, at least Disney had the courage to not play it safe and subvert the franchise a bit. This movie, in it's effort to distance itself from TLJ, is the most confusing and muddled mess of a Star Wars movie I have ever seen. I would have much rather them aggressively lean into TLJ, while sparingly taking fan complaints in mind, instead of desperately trying to act like the previous movie didn't happen. This is the worst of the new trilogy by a long shot. Does nothing new, and treats the audience like idiots with the amount of pandering and fanservice it puts on screen.

snippet.textDisplay: I actually liked The Last Jedi but the concept of undoing of TLJ didn’t bother me. ROTSW is a mess. It’s all over the place. There is no mood and pacing. It just races along in a jumbled gambled edited hodgepodge. You don’t have a moment to take anything in. Fast and yet boring. Like the Dark Rey scene: That could have been a slow, moody scene like the tree scene in Return of the Jedi. Instead it happens, lasts for 7 seconds then is over and immediately our attention goes to the next thing. No mood, no emotion. So fast yet so boring. That is the entire film. They screwed the pooch by not having a plan and I was just ready for it to end. I can’t believe I would ever say that about a Star Wars movie...

snippet.textDisplay: Anyone who gives this movie a good review is looking at the trees, not the forest. This movie is saga breaking, because it is a counter thesis to Lucas' focus on the importance of family. There is literally nothing resonant about the idea that you can choose your family name. Any bond between Rey and Kylo is purely superficial and transient, like a tinder encounter. It may be entertaining for some, but it is not important or meaningful in any way.

snippet.textDisplay: The Rise of Skywalker was a great ending to the last 3 movies but NOT the entire saga. For 6 movies we were led down a path where a "Skywalker would bring balance to the force. Either Anakin, Luke or Leia. This entire story line is about the Skywalker family..... and then the last 3 mins on this last final movie they gave it to Rey.... who "identifies" as a Skywalker. And i like the movie, love who here parents are, all the fandom throwbacks to us older generations..... but they still took a story about a specific character and changed it at the end. Fear is the path to the dark side. Fear leads to anger, anger leads to hate, hate leads to suffering..... us life long fans have suffered enough. #notmystarwars

snippet.textDisplay: I grew up with the original trilogy and fell in love. I equally adored the prequels. I have memorized details about Star Wars that most don’t know. I heard about every leak before this movie came out and seriously thought it was going to be bad. OMG, boy was I wrong. A big fat WRONG. This movie, story, visual eye candy is AMAZING. I do not feel it disregards Anakin as being the chosen one in any way like the leaks imply. It’s completely a different story 30 years later. Every Star Wars fan go go go now and see this movie. Yes there are twist. I don’t want to spoil anything. This film connects the last two films very well. I hated the TLJ but now I love it and think it even compliments this one. I even want go rewatch it. I seriously want to give a very big apology to RJ and JJ. These two directors have done an outstanding job with this trilogy. I was blind and now I see. Risks have been taken and I believe years from now they will benefit greatly from it. Disney I applaud you. To Kathleen Kennedy who I once thought should be let go and replaced, she has done an amazing job and deserves a raise. I did not understand where Disney was going with this story and at times a bit worried but man this trilogy is perfect.
